description.narrative: Output 1.4 More children, adolescents, and women, benefit from improved and equitable use of high-impact maternal, new-born, child, and adolescent nutrition-specific and sensitive interventions, which contributes to Early Childhood Development, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more vulnerable neonates, infants and children survive and thrive and fewer women die during pregnancy and childbirth
